      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 40
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine and a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission. This specimen is mechanically sorted, with the dual-VANOS system overhauled and the valves recently shimmed to factory specifications. The chassis remains rigid, benefiting from proactive rear subframe reinforcement and refreshed bushings across the multi-link rear suspension. Power is delivered to the asphalt via a factory M Variable Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution during corner exit. The engine pull is linear up to the 8,000 RPM redline, and the throttle response from the individual throttle bodies is immediate. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain and suspension geometry are dialed in for the serious driver.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 40
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Used car. Good condition. Well-maintained. Clean title. Reliable performance.",
      "price": 34500.0,
